        <h1>LeetCode 3432: Count Partitions with Even Sum Difference (C++)</h1>

        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                You are given an integer array nums of length n. A partition is defined by an index i where 0 &lt; i &lt; n. The left partition consists of elements from index 0 to i - 1, and the right partition consists of elements from index i to n - 1. The difference between the two partitions is the absolute difference between the sum of elements in the left partition and the sum of elements in the right partition. Return the number of partitions where this difference is even.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: nums = [10,10,3,7,6]<br/>
                Output: 4<br/>
                Explanation: The valid partitions are at indices 1, 2, 3, and 4.<br/><br/>
                Input: nums = [1,2,2]<br/>
                Output: 1<br/>
                Explanation: The only valid partition is at index 2.<br/><br/>
                Input: nums = [2,4,6,8]<br/>
                Output: 3<br/>
                Explanation: All partitions result in even differences.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    int countPartitions(vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; nums) {
        int n = nums.size();
        int count = 0;
        
        // Calculate total sum
        long long totalSum = 0;
        for (int num : nums) {
            totalSum += num;
        }
        
        // Calculate left sum for each partition
        long long leftSum = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i &lt; n - 1; i++) {
            leftSum += nums[i];
            long long rightSum = totalSum - leftSum;
            
            // Check if difference is even
            long long diff = abs(leftSum - rightSum);
            if (diff % 2 == 0) {
                count++;
            }
        }
        
        return count;
    }
};</code></pre>
